Color when fresh. Based on color photographs of KAUM specimens (
Fig. 2
). Body brownish, mottled with black, brown, or reddish brown, reddish blotches; irregular whitish vertical band usually present on caudal peduncle. Opercle with large black blotch, its size greater than pupil diameter (sometimes greater than orbit diameter); no distinct blotches on subopercle. Spinous portion of dorsal fin without distinct black blotch. Distal two-thirds of soft rayed portion of dorsal fin semitransparent with scattered reddish botches. Pectoral fin yellowish with numerous reddish blotches. Pelvic fin yellowish with dark red spots. Anal fin with reddish blotches basally, and reddish spots distally. Caudal fin semitransparent with scattered reddish blotches and/or spots.
